## 21. API Design Conventions

- ALWAYS version APIs: `/api/v1/...`
- ALWAYS use nouns, not verbs: `/users` not `/getUsers`
- ALWAYS return MongoDB `_id` as `id` (string) — never expose raw `_id` or `__v`
- ALWAYS paginate list endpoints: `?page=1&limit=20`
- ALWAYS validate MongoDB ObjectId params with `objectIdSchema` before querying
- ALWAYS use correct HTTP status codes:
  - `200` OK, `201` Created, `204` No Content
  - `400` Bad Request, `401` Unauthorized, `403` Forbidden
  - `404` Not Found, `409` Conflict, `422` Unprocessable Entity
  - `429` Too Many Requests, `500` Internal Server Error
- NEVER return `200` for errors

